Description: Body fragment (mended from two sherds) of North Ionian pottery double eye cup; interior: glazed with two bands of added red lined in white; exterior: two partly preserved pairs of eyes with arching eyebrows and spiral forms to denote the nose; creamy white slip on the exterior.
Curator's comments: Joins 1924,1201.900. It can be excluded that there were more than two sets of eyes.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.463)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 80, cat. Nau 15, pl. 4a)
